commit_message:
Test and document all supported Python versions

Added Python 3.6 to Travis CI test matrix.

Added all supported Pythons to list of trove classifiers. This helps
user know, at a glance, if the library is suitable for integrating with
a project.

Added:

- General Python support
- General Python 2 support
- General Python 3 support
- Python 3.6 support
- CPython support

author: Jon Dufresne
commit_message:
Pass python_requires argument to setuptools

Helps pip decide what version of the library to install.

https://packaging.python.org/tutorials/distributing-packages/#python-requires

> If your project only runs on certain Python versions, setting the
> python_requires argument to the appropriate PEP 440 version specifier
> string will prevent pip from installing the project on other Python
> versions.

https://setuptools.readthedocs.io/en/latest/setuptools.html#new-and-changed-setup-keywords

> python_requires
>
> A string corresponding to a version specifier (as defined in PEP 440)
> for the Python version, used to specify the Requires-Python defined in
> PEP 345.

commit_message:
Fix handling of different path types

In Python, a path can normally be either type bytes, str, or
pathlib.Path. Coercing a bytes object to str results in using the repr
value.

Add tests for all path types.

author: Jon Dufresne
commit_message:
Remove deprecated use of 'setup.py test'

Since setuptools v41.5.0 (27 Oct 2019), the 'test' command is formally
deprecated and should not be used. Now use unittest as the test entry
point.
